RM  23151509
RT  Microbial conversion of choline to trimethylamine requires a glycyl
RT  radical enzyme.
RA  Craciun S, Balskus EP;
RL  Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A. 2012;109:21307-21312.
CC  This system has two key enzymes for choline utilization. CutD is a
CC  radical SAM enzyme that performs a post-translational modification to
CC  activate the glycyl radical enzyme CutC. Bioinformatic, mutational, and
CC  chemical studies suggest CutC acts as a choline-TMA lyase, cleaving a
CC  C-N bond to turn choline into trimethylamine and acetaldehyde.
